{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox document | document_name = Constitution of the Year X | image = Constitution of the Year X.jpg | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = Constitution of the Year X (1802) | orig_lang_code = fr | title_orig = {{fr}} Constitution de l'an X | date_created = | date_presented = | date_ratified = 1802 | date_effective = | date_repeal = 1804 | location_of_document = | commissioned = | writer = | signers = | media_type = | subject = | purpose = }}
The '''Constitution of the Year X''' was a national [[constitution]] of [[France]] adopted during the Year X (10) of the [[French Revolutionary Calendar]] (1802 in the [[Gregorian calendar]]). It amended the [[Constitution of the Year VIII]], revising the [[French Consulate|Consulate]] to augment [[Napoleon Bonaparte]]'s authority by making him First Consul for Life.<ref>{{Cite web|title = French Legal Research — Georgetown Law|url = https://www.law.georgetown.edu/library/research/guides/frenchlegalresearch.cfm|website = www.law.georgetown.edu|accessdate = 2015-06-22}}</ref>
Both the Constitution of the Year X and the Constitution of the Year VIII were further amended by the [[Constitution of the Year XII]], which established the [[First French Empire]] with Napoleon as [[Emperor]].
