The '''Convention on the Territorial Sea and Contiguous Zone''' of 1958 is an [[international treaty]] which entered into force on 10 September 1964, one of four agreed upon at the first [[United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea]] (UNCLOS I). The convention was ratified by 52 states.<ref>[https://archive.is/20130705155944/http://treaties.un.org/Pages/ViewDetails.aspx?mtdsg_no=XXI-1&chapter=21&lang=en Ratifications].</ref>
Many states have ratified the [[UNCLOS III]] convention, which came into force in 1994 and supersedes this convention.
