{{Politics of Germany}}The '''Federal Fiscal Court''' (''Bundesfinanzhof'') is one of [[Federal courts (Germany)|five federal supreme courts]] of [[Germany]], established according to Article 95 of the [[Basic Law for the Federal Republic of Germany|Basic Law]]. It is the federal court of appeal for tax and customs matters in cases which have already been heard by the subordinate instance, namely the [[Finance Court (Germany)|Finance Courts]].

The ''Federal Fiscal Court''  was established in 1950 (succeeding the supreme Finance Court of the German Reich - ''Reichsfinanzhof'' - established in 1918). Its seat is in [[Munich]].

