{{Politics of Panama}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Panama]] on 30 August 1998.<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p518 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> Voters were asked whether they approved of amending the [[Constitution of Panama|1972 constitution]] to allow the President to be re-elected.<ref name=DN/> Only 34.3% voted in favour of the reforms,<ref name=DN>Nohlen, p525</ref> with a turnout of 65.4%.
