{{Politics of Suriname}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Suriname]] on 30 September 1987.<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p614 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> Voters were asked to approve the country's [[Constitution of Suriname|new constitution]]. It provided for a 51-seat [[unicameralism|unicameral]] [[National Assembly of Suriname|National Assembly]] elected by [[proportional representation]], a [[President of Suriname|President]] elected by the National Assembly.<ref>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=sr011987 Suriname, 30 September 1987: Constitution] Direct Democracy {{de icon}}</ref> Over 96% voted in favour, with a turnout of 62.7%.<ref>Nohlen, p615</ref>
